Author-Name: CHRISTOPHER C. GÉCZY 
Author-Name: BERNADETTE A. MINTON 
Author-Name: CATHERINE M. SCHRAND 
Title: Taking a View: Corporate Speculation, Governance, and Compensation 
Abstract:
 Using responses to a well-known confidential survey, we study
 corporations' use of derivatives to "take a view" on interest rate and
 currency movements. Characteristics of speculators suggest that perceived
 information and cost advantages lead them to take positions actively; that
 is, they do not speculate to increase risk by "betting the ranch."
 Speculating firms encourage managers to speculate through
 incentive-aligning compensation arrangements and bonding contracts, and
 they use derivatives-specific internal controls to manage potential abuse.
 Finally, we examine whether investors reading public corporate disclosures
 are able to identify firms that indicate speculating in the confidential
 survey; they are not. Copyright 2007 by The American Finance Association. 
