Author-Name: RICHARD FRIBERG 
Author-Name: MATTIAS GANSLANDT 
Title: Exchange Rates and Cash Flows in Differentiated Product Industries: A Simulation Approach 
Abstract:
 How do exchange rate changes impact firms' cash flows? We extend a
 simulation method developed in industrial organization to answer this
 question. We use prices, quantities, and product characteristics for
 differentiated products, coupled with a discrete choice framework and an
 assumption of price competition, to estimate marginal costs for all
 producers. Using a Monte Carlo approach we generate counterfactual prices
 and profits for different levels of exchange rates. We illustrate the
 method using the market for bottled water. Our results stress that even in
 a relatively simple market such as this one, different brands face very
 different exchange rate risks. Copyright 2007 by The American Finance Association. 
